## Korean translations for the authenticated dashboard surface.
##
## These were drafted alongside the Wave 3C2 i18n pass. Source-of-truth
## is the English `msgid` (legal-tech draft register); the `msgstr`
## below is the Korean rendering shown to lawyers on sprite.
##
## #. TODO native-speaker review — terms anchored on:
##   - "안건" (matter / case-file) — the canonical word for a client
##     engagement; chosen over generic "사건" (incident).
##   - "에이전트 작업" (agent run) — preserves the agent metaphor; a
##     Korean lawyer reviewer may prefer "에이전트 실행" or
##     "AI 처리". Leaving the looser "작업" as draft.
##   - "문서" stays plain; "계약서" was considered for "Documents" but
##     would be too narrow (a matter may hold evidence + memos too).
msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Language: ko\n"
"Plural-Forms: nplurals=1; plural=0;\n"

